reference "sub:Private-Auction"

\end_inset

)
\noun on
.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
After auctioning the private companies, the game consists of an alternating
 series of stock rounds interspersed by sets of one to four operating rounds
\noun on
.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The round marker is used to track of the game's progress through the rounds.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
In stock rounds, players may buy and sell shares of companies, taking and
 losing control of companies, and starting new companies (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Stock-Rounds"

\end_inset

).
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
At the end of each stock round the player order for the next stock round
 is determined by each player's remaining cash in descending order (ties
 retain the prior relative order - see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Stock-Round-General"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
In operating rounds
\noun on
,
\noun default
 companies operate: buying private companies from players, building track
 and stations, claiming or buying port markers, running and buying trains,
 and withholding or paying dividends to shareholders (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Operating-Rounds"

\end_inset

).
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Companies act in operating rounds in descending order of their stock prices
 (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Company-operating-order"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The number of operating rounds (a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

set
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

) after a stock round
\noun on
 
\noun default
is determined by the current game phase at the end of the stock round (see
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Game-Phases"

\end_inset

)
\noun on
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
At the end of each set of operating rounds, before the next stock round,
 the next available train from the supply is discarded from the game (
\emph on
bought by the foreigners)
