\begin_layout Itemize
There are four colours of track tiles: yellow, green, brown and gray.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
At the beginning of the game only yellow track tiles are available.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Yellow track tiles are placed directly on hexagons of the map.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Green track tiles upgrade/replace yellow track tiles or are used on yellow-backg
round map hexagons.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Brown track tiles upgrade/replace green track tiles.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Gray track tiles upgrade/replace brown track tiles.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Upgraded track tiles are returned to the supply for later use.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Track types
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sub:Track-types"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Outside of colour, there are three types of track tiles:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Description
City Have one or more white circles for station markers and a revenue value
 (number in a small white circle)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Description
Named
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

City Same as a normal city track tile, but marked with a city name and are
 must be used for that city's hexagon, often in a specific orientation.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Description
Paris Has two cities on the yellow map hexagon (Paris and Montparnasse)
 and three cities in green and brown (North Paris, South Paris and Montparnasse)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Description
OO
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

City Have two distinct cities on the same tile and are marked 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

OO
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 but are otherwise the same as a normal city track tile.
 Only OO city tiles can be placed on hexagons marked 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

OO
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Description
Town Have a small cross-bar or black circle marking the town with a line
 of track passing through it., and a revenue value (number in a small white
 circle).
 Town tiles are used on map hexagons containing a small black circle.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Description
Double
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

town Have two distinct track lines, each of which has a small cross-bar
 marking the separate towns.
 Double town tiles are used on map hexagons containing two small black circles.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Description
Plain Have one to four lines of track without towns or cities, which directly
 connect pairs of edges of the hexagon.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
