\begin_layout Section
Stock Market
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The stock market consists of six regions:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
A brown section in the lower left corner.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Multiple stock certificates of companies with stock price markers are in
 the brown section may be bought in a single stock round action (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Buying-shares"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Players may own more than 60% of companies with stock price markers in the
 brown section (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Buying-shares"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Stock certificates of companies with stock price markers in the brown section
 do not count against certificate limit (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Certificate-limit"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
An orange section beside the brown section in the lower left corner:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Players may own more than 60% of companies with stock price markers in the
 orange section (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Buying-shares"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Stock certificates of companies with stock price markers in the orange section
 do not count against certificate limit (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Certificate-limit"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
A yellow section beside the orange section in the lower left corner:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Stock certificates of companies with stock price markers in the yellow section
 do not count against certificate limit (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Certificate-limit"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
A large body of white stock price boxes differentiated only by value and
 with no special rules.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
A diagonal line of yellow, green, blue and brown boxes with red outlines
 that mark possible par prices for newly floated companies (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Starting-or-floating"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Game-Phases"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
A stock price of 500fr with a blue background.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The game ends if a stock price marker reaches 500fr (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Game-end"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Public companies have a stock price which is tracked on the stock market
 with a stock price marker.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When a public company is parred, its stock price marker is placed on the
 matching location on the stock market (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Starting-or-floating"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Company stock price markers move in well defined ways (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "sub:Stock-price-movement"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

